The paper focuses on relation extraction from text corpora, which is a common task in natural language processing and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a novel co-training framework that integrates distributional and pattern-based methods, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which is a popular approach in deep learning (cs.DL).
